1ï¸âƒ£ What is OSPF?
        Link-State Routing Protocol (RIP aur EIGRP jaise Distance Vector nahi).
        Open Standard hai (sab vendors use kar sakte hain, sirf Cisco tak limited nahi).
        Metric = Cost (based on Bandwidth) â†’ higher bandwidth = lower cost (better path).
        Works on Dijkstraâ€™s Shortest Path First (SPF) Algorithm.
ğŸ‘‰ Matlab: Poore network ka map banata hai aur usme se sabse short path nikalta hai.

2ï¸âƒ£ How OSPF Works (Step by Step)
        Hello Packets â†’ Routers neighbors ko discover karte hain (multicast 224.0.0.5).
        Adjacency Formation â†’ Neighbor routers ke sath relationship banata hai.
        LSA (Link State Advertisements) â†’ Har router apne connected networks ki info broadcast karta hai.
        LSDB (Link State Database) â†’ Sab routers ke paas ek hi complete network map hota hai.
        SPF Algorithm â†’ Har router apne aap best path calculate karta hai.
        Routing Table â†’ Best path ko apne routing table me daal deta hai.
ğŸ‘‰ Is wajah se OSPF fast converge karta hai aur loop-free hota hai.

3ï¸âƒ£ OSPF Areas
        Backbone Area (Area 0) â†’ Sabhi dusre areas isse connect hone chahiye.
        Normal Areas â†’ Simple internal areas.
        Stub Areas â†’ Outside routes allowed nahi, sirf default route.
        NSSA (Not-So-Stubby Area) â†’ Limited external routes allowed.
ğŸ‘‰ Areas ka use scalability ke liye hota hai (network bahut bada ho jaye to break into parts).

4ï¸âƒ£ OSPF Metric (Cost)
Formula:
        Cost = (ReferenceBandwidthCost / InterfaceBandwidth)
â€‹
 
Default Reference Bandwidth = 100 Mbps.

Example:

        FastEthernet (100 Mbps) â†’ Cost = 1
        10 Mbps link â†’ Cost = 10
        1 Gbps link â†’ Cost = 0.1 (rounded to 1 if default ref not changed)
ğŸ‘‰ Matlab hamesha fastest link ko prefer karega.

5ï¸âƒ£ OSPF Packet Types
        Hello â€“ Neighbor discovery.
        DBD (Database Description) â€“ LSDB summary exchange.
        LSR (Link State Request) â€“ Router asks for details.
        LSU (Link State Update) â€“ Router shares details.
        LSAck â€“ Acknowledgement of updates.
6ï¸âƒ£ OSPF Tables
        Neighbor Table â†’ Directly connected routers.
        Topology Table (LSDB) â†’ Full network map.
        Routing Table â†’ Best paths from LSDB.
7ï¸âƒ£ OSPF Router Types
        Internal Router â†’ Belongs to one area.
        Backbone Router â†’ Inside Area 0.
        Area Border Router (ABR) â†’ Connects multiple areas.
        Autonomous System Boundary Router (ASBR) â†’ Connects OSPF to other protocols (like BGP, RIP).
